   - Uses a range-based for loop to iterate through all elements
   - Compares each element (cast to `std::uint8_t` for compatibility with different byte types like `std::byte`) with the expected value
   - Returns `false` if any element doesn't match, `true` if all elements match

The implementation leverages C++20 features (auto parameters) and ensures compile-time array generation with constexpr.

