```cpp
#include <hexi/exception.h>
#include <string>
#include <cstddef>

struct ExceptionDetails {
    std::size_t read_size;
    std::size_t total_read;
    std::size_t limit_or_size;
    std::string message;
};

ExceptionDetails extract_underrun_info(const hexi::buffer_underrun& e) {
    return ExceptionDetails{
        e.read_size,
        e.total_read,
        e.buff_size,
        e.what()
    };
}

ExceptionDetails extract_read_limit_info(const hexi::stream_read_limit& e) {
    return ExceptionDetails{
        e.read_size,
        e.total_read,
        e.read_limit,
        e.what()
    };
}

std::string get_exception_message(const hexi::exception& e) {
    return e.what();
}
```

## Explanation:

1. **`extract_underrun_info`**: Accesses the public fields of `hexi::buffer_underrun`:
   - `e.read_size` - the requested read size
   - `e.total_read` - total bytes read so far
   - `e.buff_size` - the buffer size (stored in `limit_or_size`)
   - `e.what()` - the formatted error message

2. **`extract_read_limit_info`**: Accesses the public fields of `hexi::stream_read_limit`:
   - `e.read_size` - the requested read size
   - `e.total_read` - total bytes read so far
   - `e.read_limit` - the read limit (stored in `limit_or_size`)
   - `e.what()` - the formatted error message

3. **`get_exception_message`**: Returns the error message from any `hexi::exception` using the standard `what()` method.

